      "text": "Boredom is a state of mind, not a need for nicotine — there's nothing in a cigarette that relieves it. What actually happened was this: when you were bored, your mind was unoccupied, so there was nothing distracting you from the faint nag of the monster, and you fed it almost without noticing. The cigarette didn't make the boredom interesting; it just gave the restlessness somewhere to land. Watch any bored smoker and you'll see it — they smoke, and they still look bored.\n\nThere's a sharper edge to it too: smoking actually deepened boredom over time. The drug leaves you a little lethargic and flat, so instead of getting up and doing something engaging, you slump and feed the monster. The cigarette was both the filler of empty time and a cause of more empty time. As a non-smoker, your energy and drive return — which makes the idle moments easier to fill with something real."
